<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-07T19:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-07T19:29:00-05:00" n="859" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/833: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-07T19:00:00-05:29"><hi rend="italic">September 7,
                                        1922—7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 10:13
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>59. Referring to your 61, September 6, paragraph three. Mr. Meyer,<note n="48" xml:id="d859fn48">Secretary of American Legation at
                                Habana.</note> after personal conference with Secretary Despaigne,
                            reports this evening that the revenues for the months of July and August
                            exceeded the budget obligations for those months by $527,000.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>